bits.strings

Class BitStringArraySplitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • bits.Problem
      • bits.strings.BitStringArraySplitter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IProblem, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>

    public class BitStringArraySplitter
extends Problem
implements IProblem
    Two constraints are imposed by this IProblem:

    1. S1 and S2 are bitwise negations of each other;

    2. For each i, X[i] is not dominated* by S1;

    3. For each i, X[i] is not dominated by S2;

    An equivalent statement is that S1 and S2 split each X[i] into nonzero IBitStrings whose bitwise AND is the zero IBitString.

    *We say that IBitString X is dominated by IBitString Y if and only if the bitwise AND of X and Y equals X.
